A NULL Pointer Dereference vulnerability in TP-Link Archer BE400 V1(802.11 modules) allows&nbsp;

<span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">an adjacent attacker to cause a denial-of-service (DoS) by triggering a device reboot.</span>

<p>This issue affects Archer BE400: xi 1.1.0 Build 20250710 rel.14914.</p>
